# BudgetSparrow does not require any client-side env vars for normal operation.
#
# Receipt OCR is handled by a server-side Cloudflare Worker endpoint at
# /api/scan-receipt. The Azure subscription key lives on the Worker only —
# it does NOT ship in the client bundle. Set these variables in the
# Cloudflare dashboard (Workers & Pages → your project → Settings → Variables):
#
#   AZURE_DOC_INTEL_ENDPOINT     https://YOUR-RESOURCE.cognitiveservices.azure.com
#   AZURE_DOC_INTEL_KEY          (mark as Secret / encrypted)
#   AZURE_DOC_INTEL_MODEL        prebuilt-receipt          (optional)
#   AZURE_DOC_INTEL_API_VERSION  2024-11-30                (optional)
#   ALLOWED_ORIGINS              https://your.deployed.domain   (optional;
#                                comma-separated; if unset all origins pass)
#
# These are runtime Worker variables, NOT VITE_-prefixed build-time vars.
# Do not commit real values anywhere — the GitHub repo is public.
